    "units": [
        {
            "id": "unit-gd-01",
            "title": "Module 1: Design Principles",
            "order": 1,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "gd-s01",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "The Elements of Design",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>7 Elements of Design</h2><p>Every design is built from these fundamentals:</p><ol><li><strong>Line</strong> — direction, movement, separation</li><li><strong>Shape</strong> — geometric or organic forms</li><li><strong>Color</strong> — emotion, hierarchy, branding</li><li><strong>Texture</strong> — visual or tactile quality</li><li><strong>Space</strong> — negative &amp; positive space</li><li><strong>Type</strong> — font choice and hierarchy</li><li><strong>Image</strong> — photography, illustration</li></ol>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "gd-s02",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "interactive",
                    "title": "Color Theory",
                    "content": {
                        "interaction_type": "accordion",
                        "instructions": "Learn color theory by opening each section.",
                        "completion_condition": "all_panels_opened",
                        "panels": [
                            {
                                "id": "gdp1",
                                "label": "Color Wheel",
                                "html": "<p><strong>Primary</strong>: Red, Blue, Yellow<br><strong>Secondary</strong>: Orange, Green, Purple<br><strong>Tertiary</strong>: Mixes of primary + secondary</p>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "gdp2",
                                "label": "Color Harmony",
                                "html": "<ul><li><strong>Complementary</strong>: Opposite colors (red + green)</li><li><strong>Analogous</strong>: Adjacent colors (blue, blue-green, green)</li><li><strong>Triadic</strong>: Three equally spaced colors</li></ul>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "gdp3",
                                "label": "Color Psychology",
                                "html": "<ul><li>🔴 Red — energy, urgency, passion</li><li>🔵 Blue — trust, calm, professionalism</li><li>🟡 Yellow — optimism, attention, caution</li><li>🟢 Green — growth, health, nature</li></ul>"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "gd-s03",
                    "order": 3,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Typography",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Typography Fundamentals</h2><p>Type communicates before it is even read. Key concepts:</p><ul><li><strong>Typefaces</strong>: Serif (Times), Sans-serif (Arial), Display, Script</li><li><strong>Hierarchy</strong>: Differentiate headings, body, captions using size and weight</li><li><strong>Kerning</strong>: Space between individual letters</li><li><strong>Leading</strong>: Space between lines (line-height)</li><li><strong>Rule of thumb</strong>: Use maximum 2-3 typefaces per design</li></ul>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "unit-gd-02",
            "title": "Module 2: Tools & Practice",
            "order": 2,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "gd-s04",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Design Tools",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Popular Design Tools</h2><ul><li><strong>Canva</strong> — beginner-friendly, browser-based, free tier</li><li><strong>Adobe Photoshop</strong> — photo editing &amp; raster graphics</li><li><strong>Adobe Illustrator</strong> — vector graphics &amp; logos</li><li><strong>Figma</strong> — UI/UX design, collaboration, prototyping</li></ul><p>Start with <strong>Canva</strong> to practice design principles without a steep learning curve.</p>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "gd-s05",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Design Workflow",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>The Design Process</h2><ol><li><strong>Brief</strong> — understand the objective and audience</li><li><strong>Research</strong> — competitors, inspiration (Behance, Dribbble)</li><li><strong>Sketch</strong> — rough wireframes on paper</li><li><strong>Design</strong> — create in your chosen tool</li><li><strong>Feedback</strong> — iterate with client or stakeholder</li><li><strong>Export</strong> — correct formats (PNG, SVG, PDF)</li></ol>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
